# Open deploy gates — manual prod steps that code alone can't satisfy.
# The pre-push hook (.git/hooks/pre-push) prints every [ ] block before a push
# to master, so these aren't forgotten. Tick a box to [x] once done; checked
# gates stay quiet. This is a reminder, never a block.

[x] Supabase email templates include {{ .Token }}  (added 2026-06-16, done 2026-06-16)
    Why: BOTH email doors now use Supabase native email OTP — the QR door step
    (DoorVerify) AND the standard wall (AuthCard, magic-link retired). Without
    {{ .Token }} in the "Magic Link" AND "Confirm signup" templates, the email
    sends only a link — no 6-digit code — and neither door can complete.
    Where: Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Email Templates.

[ ] (optional) WhatsApp OTP login — flip VITE_DOOR_WHATSAPP_OTP=true once Meta
    approves the auth-OTP template, then rebuild the FE. ONE flag now lights
    BOTH surfaces: whatsappLoginEnabled() (lib/useAuthOrder.js) honors either
    VITE_DOOR_WHATSAPP_OTP or VITE_WHATSAPP_LOGIN_ENABLED. Once lit, the adaptive
    resolver auto-leads with WhatsApp for phone-first arrivals (Nairobi etc.);
    until then it's correctly dropped (never an inert/failing option). Backend
    phone-person linking already wired (ensurePersonLinkedByPhone).

[ ] LIVE SMOKE TEST — loginOnly email-code path (do once, can't verify headless):
    on the waitlist-gated login wall, AuthCard now sends the email OTP with
    shouldCreateUser:false and maps Supabase's signups-disallowed error to
    { exists:false } → waitlist handoff. Confirm with a real round-trip that
    (a) a KNOWN email gets a code + signs in, and (b) an UNKNOWN email routes to
    the waitlist (not a stuck code screen). Tighten the error match in
    AuthContext.sendEmailCode if Supabase's actual error shape differs.
